page.title: 10St.Pauls Cray-housing.
page.content: Most of the houses close to the Walsingham School were originally built by the Council,but many have been bought by the occupiers and are now privately owned.These have been improved by changing windows and doors,adding garages and building extensions onto the original house.In roads like St.Pauls Wood Hill,a lot of money has been spent on making them look nice by pebble-dashing and adding porches. There are a few detached houses and bungalows,many more semi-detached and terraced houses and flats.Nearly all the houses have reasonably sized gardens.Most houses and gardens are well kept,but there is the odd scruffy house.There are a few garages.Most roads are busy and have cars parked at the kerb,but there is plenty of green space around to make the area pleasant.
